  <h2>Final thoughts</h2>
  <p>
    A good pantry setup should make cooking and shopping easier, not add another system to
    maintain. Clear out what is expired, group food by routine, measure the shelves and then
    choose storage for the awkward parts.
  </p>
  <p>
    Baskets, containers, labels, shelf risers and turntables can all help, but only when they
    solve a real problem. Improve one shelf or category at a time and the pantry will become
    easier to use without needing a kitchen redesign.
  </p>

